    • Field Detail

      • nodeID

        public final int nodeID
        Unique node ID

      • rootPath

        protected final List<Integer> rootPath
        Sequence of the IDs of the nodes encountered while walking from the root of the BAP tree to this node. rootPath[0]=0, rootPath[last(rootPath)]=this.nodeID

      • branchingDecisions

        protected final List<BranchingDecision> branchingDecisions
        List of branching decisions that lead to this node.

      • initialColumns

        protected final List<U extends AbstractColumn<T,?>> initialColumns
        Columns used to initialize the master problem

      • initialInequalities

        protected final List<AbstractInequality> initialInequalities
        Valid inequalities used to initialize the master problem of this node

      • objective

        protected double objective
        Objective value of the master problem after solving this node.

      • bound

        protected double bound
        Bound on the optimum solution of this node. If the bound of this node exceeds the best incumbent int solution, this node will be pruned. If this node is solved to optimality, this.objective and this.bound must be equal

      • solution

        protected List<U extends AbstractColumn<T,?>> solution
        List of columns constituting the solution after solving this node; Typically, only non-zero columns are stored

      • inequalities

        protected List<AbstractInequality> inequalities
        List of inequalities in the master problem after solving this node

    • Constructor Detail

      • BAPNode

        public BAPNode(int nodeID,
               List<Integer> rootPath,
               List<U> initialColumns,
               List<AbstractInequality> initialInequalities,
               double bound,
               List<BranchingDecision> branchingDecisions)
        Creates a new BAPNode
        Parameters:
        nodeID - ID of the Node
        rootPath - Sequence of the IDs of the nodes encountered while walking from the root of the BAP tree to this node. rootPath[0]=0, rootPath[last(rootPath)]=this.nodeID
        initialColumns - Columns used to initialize the master problem
        initialInequalities - Valid inequalities used to initialize the master problem of this node
        bound - Bound on the optimum solution of this node. If the bound of this node exceeds the best incumbent integer solution, this node will be pruned. The bound may be inherited from the parent.
        branchingDecisions - List of branching decisions that lead to this node.

    • Method Detail

      • getParentID

        public int getParentID()
        Returns the ID of its parent in the Branch-and-Price tree. For memory efficiency, no pointer to the ancestor is returned. As maintaining a link to every parent may be expensive.
        Returns:
        ID of parent node, or -1 if this is the root node

      • getBranchingDecision

        public BranchingDecision getBranchingDecision()
        Returns the branching decision that produced this particular node.
        Returns:
        The branching decision that links this node to its parent, or null if this node is the root node

      • addInitialColumns

        public void addInitialColumns(List<U> additionalColumns)
        Adds initial columns to this node. When the node is solved, these columns will be added to the master problem. This method may be invoked multiple times to add additional columns.
        Parameters:
        additionalColumns - columns to add to the initial solution.

      • addInitialInequalities

        public void addInitialInequalities(List<AbstractInequality> additionalInequalities)
        Adds initial inequalities to this node. When the node is solved, these inequalities will be added to the master problem. This method may be invoked multiple times to add additional inequalities.
        Parameters:
        additionalInequalities - columns to add to the initial solution.

      • setObjective

        public void setObjective(double objective)
        After the node has been solved, this method is used to record the objective of the solution
        Parameters:
        objective - solution objective

      • setBound

        public void setBound(double bound)
        After the node has been solved, this method is used to record the bound on the objective value of this node.
        Parameters:

      • getInitialColumns

        public List<U> getInitialColumns()

        Returns:
        a set of columns which are used to initialize the master problem when this node is being solved.

      • getInitialInequalities

        a set of inequalities which are used to initialize the master problem when this node is being solved.
